Police Minister Fikile Mbalula has elevated Hawks deputy national head Yolisa Matakata to the position of acting head of the unit. CAPE TOWN - Police Minister Fikile Mbalula has appointed Hawks deputy commissioner Yolisa Matakata as the acting head of the unit until further notice.The decision follows the High Court ruling on Wednesday that Berning Ntlemeza may no longer hold the position as head of the Hawks.In 2015, the courts found that Ntlemeza lied under oath and lacked integrity.Mbalula relied on provisions in the SAPS Act which allowed for the Hawks deputy to act as the head of the unit.Mbalula says the Hawks need to be turned around.More to follow.